commit_message:
Remove disruptive actions from run-playbooks

This removes the following actions from run-playbooks:

- Existing container restarts
  When executing run-playbooks on an existing environment this is
  especially disruptive to Galera/RabbitMQ clusters as the restart
  is not done in serial.

- veth cleanup
  This action was put in place prior to the implementation of named
  veths and the ARP flush implemented within the containers. The
  action is therefore no longer required.

- Net cache flush
  This action was put in place prior to the implementation of the
  ARP flush implemented within the containers. The action is
  therefore no longer required.

- Force the restart of the conatiner networks
  This action was put in place prior to the implementation of the
  ARP flush implemented within the containers. The action is
  therefore no longer required.

- Force an apt-cache update for packages and keys
  This action was added before the update to the container build
  process which already does this, and before the diagnosis of the
  issue in hpcloud-b4. This action therefore just causing an
  unnecessary delay in the execution of the playbooks.

Change-Id: I6140b94ccb339b5b394acabfa97304813b0b2ab6

subject: Docs: encourage users to run apt-get dist-upgrade on target hosts
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-02-02 18:15:05.000000000', 'files': ['doc/source/developer-docs/quickstart-aio.rst', 'doc/source/install-guide/targethosts-prepare.rst'], 'message': "Docs: encourage users to run apt-get dist-upgrade on target hosts

Ubuntu 14.04 is currently provided in several point releases, most
currently 14.04.3.  It is possible that users may initially deploy
roles on a previous point release of Ubuntu, and then later upgrade
system packages.  Most notably, br_netfilter is implemented in it's
own kernel module in kernel versions >= 3.18.  This results in ansible
fact caches being out of date on subsequent runs, and has caused a few
bugs to be filed along the way.

This patch is to hopefully ensure that users are using the most recent

Change-Id: I1fd4f11fc2e4be4fa4335f63031f7b2bdb312d34
Closes-Bug: #1535075
"}]
commit_message:
Docs: encourage users to run apt-get dist-upgrade on target hosts

Ubuntu 14.04 is currently provided in several point releases, most
currently 14.04.3.  It is possible that users may initially deploy
roles on a previous point release of Ubuntu, and then later upgrade
system packages.  Most notably, br_netfilter is implemented in it's
own kernel module in kernel versions >= 3.18.  This results in ansible
fact caches being out of date on subsequent runs, and has caused a few
bugs to be filed along the way.

This patch is to hopefully ensure that users are using the most recent
version of packages when beginning with openstack-ansible.

Change-Id: I1fd4f11fc2e4be4fa4335f63031f7b2bdb312d34
Closes-Bug: #1535075

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-02-01 21:01:46.000000000', 'files': ['nova/api/openstack/compute/floating_ips.py'], 'message': 'Optimize the instance fetched by floating_ips API

The floating_ips API fetches an instance without flavor information
and then passes it to the Network API, which eventually calls
_get_instrance_nw_info() which requires access to the flavor. This
triggers a lazy load in 100% of the situations, which is really not
necessary and wasteful.

This patch adds flavor to the list of pre-queried attributes on the
instances fetched by this API to help reduce that waste.

Change-Id: I15eae4e8c03739a34cef9c90989ad0615a96a963
Partial-Bug: #1540526
'}]
commit_message:
Optimize the instance fetched by floating_ips API

The floating_ips API fetches an instance without flavor information
and then passes it to the Network API, which eventually calls
_get_instrance_nw_info() which requires access to the flavor. This
triggers a lazy load in 100% of the situations, which is really not
necessary and wasteful.

This patch adds flavor to the list of pre-queried attributes on the
instances fetched by this API to help reduce that waste.

Change-Id: I15eae4e8c03739a34cef9c90989ad0615a96a963
Partial-Bug: #1540526

commit_message:
Zoom out pages in i9n tests

Since Selenium 2.50.1 release it's no longer possible to click
elements which are outside of visible viewport. To keep both tests
working and error screenshots still visible, standard xvfb screensize
is set to 1920x1080 and page scale is set to 67%.

Also temporarily disable create_instance test since it fails on some
nodes due to missing network.

Related-Bug: #1542211
Closes-Bug: #1541876
Change-Id: Ie96606cf52860dd8bb3286971962a16cb3415daf

commit_message:
Fix django warning

When launching the server, the following message appears:

RemovedInDjango110Warning: django.conf.urls.patterns() is deprecated
and will be removed in Django 1.10. Update your urlpatterns to be a
list of django.conf.urls.url() instances instead.

This commit fix this warning in app-catalog/openstack_catalog/urls.py:7

Change-Id: Id3ba43d9ce2d81985a66adfecc06c3102a14a94f

subject: change delete volume flag
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-12-16 04:25:42.000000000', 'files': ['trove/taskmanager/models.py'], 'message': 'change delete volume flag

Recently I found when delete the instance,it always call the cinder to 
delete the volume that attach to the server.But this flag means delete 
volume when server is deleted,and instance is resize-volumed ,cinderclient will come with excetion.
So change the flag from True to False,the cinderclient always will be
ok.
Change-Id: I4139b82b44e2cb8acce654d3e0af6be69e614326
'}]
commit_message:
change delete volume flag

Recently I found when delete the instance,it always call the cinder to 
delete the volume that attach to the server.But this flag means delete 
volume when server is deleted,and instance is resize-volumed ,cinderclient will come with excetion.
So change the flag from True to False,the cinderclient always will be
ok.
Change-Id: I4139b82b44e2cb8acce654d3e0af6be69e614326

subject: Make Rally cope with unversioned keystone URL
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 8491, 'name': 'Illia Khudoshyn', 'email': 'ikhudoshyn@mirantis.com', 'username': 'ikhudoshyn'}, {'_account_id': 9545, 'name': 'Andriy Kurilin', 'email': 'andr.kurilin@gmail.com', 'username': 'akurilin'}, {'_account_id': 10475, 'name': 'Alexander Maretskiy', 'email': 'amaretskiy@mirantis.com', 'username': 'maretskiy'}, {'_account_id': 11748, 'name': 'Chris St. Pierre', 'email': 'cstpierr@cisco.com', 'username': 'stpierre'}, {'_account_id': 14817, 'name': 'Mirantis Rally CI', 'email': 'rally-ci@mirantis.com', 'username': 'ci50'}, {'_account_id': 15750, 'name': 'Julian Edwards', 'email': 'bigjools@gmail.com', 'username': 'bigjools'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 7, 'created': '2016-02-04 12:21:07.000000000', 'files': ['tests/unit/test_osclients.py', 'rally/osclients.py'], 'message': "Make Rally cope with unversioned keystone URL

The way in which OSClient was constructing a keystone client was flawed
and using a deprecated method. It was also second guessing the
discovery process, which keystoneclient itself can handle on its own.

The main symptom of the flawed approach was that you were unable to use
keystone URLs in the catalog that didn't have the version appended,
e.g.:
  * http://foo.rally:5000/v3
  versus
  * http://foo.rally:5000/

The latter form is the correct form according to the Keystone
developers I spoke to.

With the change, the client version that's returned is now determined by
the keystoneclient library itself based on whether you supply a URL
with a version in it or not.

Change-Id: I3fc6f7b9724922ab7d47ce371578897da611b455
"}]
commit_message:
Make Rally cope with unversioned keystone URL

The way in which OSClient was constructing a keystone client was flawed
and using a deprecated method. It was also second guessing the
discovery process, which keystoneclient itself can handle on its own.

The main symptom of the flawed approach was that you were unable to use
keystone URLs in the catalog that didn't have the version appended,
e.g.:
  * http://foo.rally:5000/v3
  versus
  * http://foo.rally:5000/

The latter form is the correct form according to the Keystone
developers I spoke to.

With the change, the client version that's returned is now determined by
the keystoneclient library itself based on whether you supply a URL
with a version in it or not.

Change-Id: I3fc6f7b9724922ab7d47ce371578897da611b455

commit_message:
Add check requirements job to octavia

Octavia does get the bot proposed updates, but does not have the job
that checks if proposed updates to requirements.txt are in
global-requirements. As a result ndg-httpsclient was added in:
If51b19dc6b6d13eda734b08de91700378f6e1e89

even though it has not been approved yet in g-r:
Id233df6061da47bd28f543615b6bf2a75e29a6cb

commit_message:
DB fields added to action_logs for SQL speedup

On the 1M number of rows in the table JSON index begins to
work too slow. We are copy action_name and action_type values
from action_logs.body to separate indexed columns in the
action_logs table.

Redundant JSON serialization/deserealization on the python
level is removed by changing column 'structure' type from
TEXT to JSON in the InstallationStrurcure model. We already
had JSON data in 'structure' in the DB, thus only SQLAlchemy
model is changed.

Change-Id: I415f4fe607f44ac670f63f961af7fb4998f75dd6
Closes-Bug: #1540289

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-02-03 08:57:23.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/tests/unit/agent/linux/test_dhcp.py', 'neutron/agent/linux/dhcp.py'], 'message': 'DHCP: fix regression with DNS nameservers

The commit 3686d035ded94eadab6a3268e4b0f0cca11a22f8 caused a
regression for setups that support a number of DNS servers that
are injected via the DHCP options 5 and 6.

If the dnsmaq has a configured dns-server then it will ignore
the ones that are injected by the admin. That is what the commit
above did. This causes a number of problems. The main one is that
it requires the DHCP agent to have connectivity to the DNS server.

The original code was added in commit
2afff147c45f97a0809db40ad072332fb37ccd8d

Change-Id: Iae3e994533102a2b076cc2dc205cdd5caaee1206
Closes-bug: #1540960
'}]
commit_message:
DHCP: fix regression with DNS nameservers

The commit 3686d035ded94eadab6a3268e4b0f0cca11a22f8 caused a
regression for setups that support a number of DNS servers that
are injected via the DHCP options 5 and 6.

If the dnsmaq has a configured dns-server then it will ignore
the ones that are injected by the admin. That is what the commit
above did. This causes a number of problems. The main one is that
it requires the DHCP agent to have connectivity to the DNS server.

The original code was added in commit
2afff147c45f97a0809db40ad072332fb37ccd8d

Change-Id: Iae3e994533102a2b076cc2dc205cdd5caaee1206
Closes-bug: #1540960

commit_message:
Allow ceph-disk activate-all to return errors

`ceph-disk activate-all` is used in conjuction with `udevadm trigger`
to prevent allready prepapred/provisioned disks from being re-formatted.

The error expressed in bug: 1541946 is that activate-all has errors
because there is no filesystem on the devices. This is accurate on nodes
where the OSD was not previously sucessful. To combat this we should
allow for the command to return errors

Change-Id: I5cf29fcba7b0443832489c90518a9197c065ac8c
Closes-bug: 1541946

commit_message:
Use http request to check cinder api availability

Using a port open check is not reliable when going through a load
balancer.

httplib2 is added as it is required by the Ansible uri module.

Change-Id: I0e489e8f671b262c56c1442e7af85fd53c061598
Closes-bug: #1525208

commit_message:
Remove useless indexes

For all tables an index (with unique=False) is created for the primary key
when the database already creates an index (with unique=True)

This change keeps the primary key index and drop the other one.

Change-Id: I5fec9692679d8f2f2176865e874f0c8676e15929

commit_message:
Rename kolla_ansible to kolla_toolbox

This change is needed for clarity. We have a kolla-ansible script.
We have a kolla-mesos repo. We plan to have a kolla-ansible repo.
Already we have had far too much confusion about whether we are
talking about the container or the project. Naming this kolla-toolbox
eliminates all of that confusion and its probably a bit more accurate
of a name too.

Closes-Bug: #1541053
Change-Id: I8fd1f49d5a22b36ede5b10f46b9fe02ddda9007e

commit_message:
Add popular IP protocols for security group

Add these additional protocols listed below to
security groups brings convenience to operators
on configuring these protocols. In addition, make
the security group rules more readable.

The added protocols are: ah, dccp, egp, esp, gre,
ipv6-encap, ipv6-frag, ipv6-nonxt, ipv6-opts,
ipv6-route, ospf, pgm, rsvp, sctp, udplite, vrrp.

A related patch is submitted to neutron-lib project:
https://review.openstack.org/259037

DocImpact: You can specify protocol names rather than
protocol number in API and CLI commands. I'll update
the documentation when it is merged.

APIImpact

Change-Id: Iaef9b650449b4d9d362a59305c45e0aa3831507c
Closes-Bug: #1475717

commit_message:
Changed JSON on Mutable(Dict/List) in Cluster object

Changed all JSON fields in Cluster on corresponding Mutable(Dict/List)
Fixed default value of replaced_deployment_info field on [] due to
expectations of TestReplacedDataMigration test, that declares that
replaced_deployment_info field is a list object.

commit_message:
Remove references to SERVERS_CONSOLIDATION

Change I6c43eba941022a88851a199b56a6c20f017b9e71 seemed to have remove
most references to the SERVERS_CONSOLIDATION goal.  Since this goal does
not currently exist in the actual code and all usages of it are for
samples or for tests, it is replaced with the DUMMY goal to avoid
confusion.

Closes-Bug: #1538388

commit_message:
Add generated port id to port dict

Port id generated in create_port was not populated back to port_dict.
As a result port id information was not available on
AddressRequestFactory level (used by 3rd party ipam providers).

This fix populates port_id into copied port dict (to prevent affecting
incoming port dict).
Added UT to make sure that port id is added to port dict which is passed
to AddressFactory.

Change-Id: I62e4d9e887488b9ceeafb90b044f95a22c1765b0
Closes-Bug: #1527089

commit_message:
Adding auditing support for API request using audit middleware

This change adds audit filter in paste ini file which can be used to add
this filter in existing request processing pipeline.  Added new pipeline
with audit filter after keystone_authtoken filter.

Adding documentation about how to use this.

This change provides auditing on REST API side. Worker side changes will
be done later in another review and are not dependent on this.

Change-Id: I308796f5804aa55bc3d6496ded0504b469f00301
Partially-Implements: blueprint audit-cadf-events

subject: Translate resource_id to UUID5 format.
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-02-05 11:31:12.000000000', 'files': ['gnocchiclient/utils.py', 'gnocchiclient/tests/functional/test_resource.py', 'gnocchiclient/v1/metric.py', 'gnocchiclient/v1/resource.py'], 'message': 'Translate resource_id to UUID5 format.

Due to wsgi spec issue, webserver and webob decode "%2F" into "/" for PATH_INFO.
Some webserver allows to change this behavior, but webob doesn't.
Until we find a suitable better solution I propose that the client
always translate the resource_id in uuid5 format.

Related-bug: #1500890
Change-Id: Id3df57a54ad35b12e691eff2d4d3c40effe1f808
'}]
commit_message:
Translate resource_id to UUID5 format.

Due to wsgi spec issue, webserver and webob decode "%2F" into "/" for PATH_INFO.
Some webserver allows to change this behavior, but webob doesn't.
Until we find a suitable better solution I propose that the client
always translate the resource_id in uuid5 format.

Related-bug: #1500890
Change-Id: Id3df57a54ad35b12e691eff2d4d3c40effe1f808

commit_message:
[multirack] Check VIP allocation after deployment

In the tests for multiple cluster networks were controllers
are assigned to non-default nodegroup, we check that VIPs
are allocated from non-default nodegroup too.
Currently it's impossible to get VIPs before environment
deployment, so that check is moved to the last step.

Change-Id: I7c6dcc545151471a7d2c2c1d7c54c0a758bbbfa2
Closes-bug: #1541921

commit_message:
Move allocation outside try except block

Unless ips are returned by _allocate_ips_for_port there is nothing to
deallocate, so moving this part outside try except block.
Failure inside _allocate_ips_for_port is handled separatetely by
rollback-on-failure logic in _ipam_allocate_ips.

Change-Id: Ic592f7edc7b1ddd5c352eabe707147f704e6e197

commit_message:
[multirack] Check VIP allocation after deplpoyment

In the tests for multiple cluster networks were controllers
are assigned to non-default nodegroup, we check that VIPs
are allocated from non-default nodegroup too.
Currently it's impossible to get VIPs before environment
deployment, so that check is moved to the last step.

Change-Id: I7c6dcc545151471a7d2c2c1d7c54c0a758bbbfa2
Closes-bug: #1541921

commit_message:
Using dict.items() is better than six.iteritems(dict)

Replacing dict.iteritems()/.itervalues() with
six.iteritems(dict)/six.itervalues(dict) was preferred in the past,
but there was a discussion suggesting to avoid six for this[1].

[1]http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/066391.html

subject: Create periodic status task to check dhcp agents in Ovn Worker
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-02-02 08:56:46.000000000', 'files': ['networking_ovn/plugin.py'], 'message': 'Create periodic status task to check dhcp agents in Ovn Worker

This is moved from the parent neutron process plugin to
Ovn Worker process because
 - dhcp agent scheduler calls plugin.port_update to reschedule a network
   from a dead dhcp agent to active one and OvsdbOvnIdl object
   (self._ovn) is not created in the main neutron process plugin object.
   This results in the AttributeError exception.
 - OvsdbOvnIdl object is created only in the worker processes.
 - Ovn worker seems to be the right candidate.

Alternate solution is to create the OvsdbOvnIdl object in
OVNPlugin.__init__()

Closes-bug: #1536004
Change-Id: I4246728cc4c9800b05c9c3d1d691590a9b221051
'}]
commit_message:
Create periodic status task to check dhcp agents in Ovn Worker

This is moved from the parent neutron process plugin to
Ovn Worker process because
 - dhcp agent scheduler calls plugin.port_update to reschedule a network
   from a dead dhcp agent to active one and OvsdbOvnIdl object
   (self._ovn) is not created in the main neutron process plugin object.
   This results in the AttributeError exception.
 - OvsdbOvnIdl object is created only in the worker processes.
 - Ovn worker seems to be the right candidate.

Alternate solution is to create the OvsdbOvnIdl object in
OVNPlugin.__init__()

Closes-bug: #1536004
Change-Id: I4246728cc4c9800b05c9c3d1d691590a9b221051

commit_message:
Add logic to error out of key creation if order errors out

The Barbican back end contains a timeout loop during key creation
to return the key's UUID only if the Barbican order status is ACTIVE.
This loop waits for ACTIVE status, but it should also exit the loop if
an ERROR status is found.

Change-Id: I8282f3929dcdf68b438285eb0dde884b36ec6c3b

commit_message:
Experimental periodic jobs for testing against oslo.* from master

Starting with Nova (from master), we'd like to test py27 and py34
tox targets against oslo.* from master branch on a daily basis.
Once we get this stabilized we can add other projects as well.
Note that we only test master of a project against oslo.* master
in the two jobs defined in this review.

Change-Id: I82ef7a5d5a3c1076efbd4306b7099cd28960cd90

commit_message:
Correct the bandit test dependency

Anchor currently fixes the version of bandit to use as 0.10.0.
And because it was in a separate test-bandit-requirements.txt file,
the OpenStack proposal bot never updated it.

This change removes the separate file and merges into regular test
requirements.  As a result, bandit version will jump to 0.17.3

Change-Id: I0988f603d20a2bd21928d1bf009e32db901168a2

commit_message:
Reap idle SQL connections after 60 seconds

Set the default time to reap idle SQL connections to 60 seconds.

This is a change from the old default of 1 hour, which will result in
far fewer idle connections on potentially busy DB servers after short
periods of load.

Change-Id: I2031a4a07aea321804eda58d980d8eee578d983d

commit_message:
POC of fuel-main tests.

This is a simple test scenario with
many things to change:
test framework, fuel-main compatibility
for tests, choice of virtualization/
containerization.

Currently it executes ks.template, which
is bash script, with huge amount of errors
in docker environment (carefully check for
breakouts from docker). Then result is parsed
and checked against expected behaviour.

Result of command
"date;time docker run -v `pwd`:/etc/iso -it ubuntu:14.04 /bin/bash /etc/iso/tests/run.sh;date"
is:
Mon Aug 31 16:57:02 MSK 2015
 ✓ When no parameters to ks script
 ✓ When parameter admin_interface=eth3 to ks script

2 tests, 0 failures
docker run -v `pwd`:/etc/iso -it ubuntu:14.04 /bin/bash /etc/iso/tests/run.sh  0.02s user 0.01s system 0% cpu 47.442 total
Mon Aug 31 16:57:49 MSK 2015

That shows that minimal fuel-main verification
can be done in less than a minute.

Change-Id: If5c356f888b73a79acf78b2af94fd5203692f3a0

change will make it so configuration can be tested with normal

commit_message:
Convert the gate to OCC

Currently, the gate uses all environment variables and it would
be easier to set up two OCC environments for v2 and v3 identity
testing.  A couple things about this change:

* I created a functional/gate.sh so it would be easier to test
  the script.
* It uses command line options to set various api versions
  rather than environment variables.  I think the environment
  variables could effect the outcome of other tests.
* One reason we need two OCC environments is OSC does not
  support v2 authentication with v3 identity commands.
* Auto detection of auth type is broken because auth_type is
  defaulted, so it never makes it through the code bug/1489913.
* Command line options like --os-auth-url are broken, there is
  another bug for that bug/1489917.

So, some of this can be cleaned up when the bugs get fixed.

Change-Id: I3e06c38fe4e27efc63b6cac5d696e83207c12b7b

commit_message:
Allow override debug default and help text

Allow applications to override the debug default value and
help text.  Since argparse doesn't support a get, it is basically
impossible for an application to modify these arguments.  OSC
uses --debug to mean stacktrace *and* verbose=3.  Also, OCC
will not allow debug to be set in the log file if it is defaulted
to False.

Closes-Bug: #1483378

Change-Id: I4fdb1c11075d08e2d1b9bcb9976aec962d645d49

commit_message:
Refactor remove_router_interface() for DVR

Currently this method duplicates code from l3_db, looks complicated
and hard to read.
The patch refactors it to reuse code from l3_db just adding needed
dvr related handling.
New methods (introduced by parent patch) were used to know which dvr agents
should router be deleted from. This will be needed when we remove explicit
binding of dvr agents to routers in later patches.

The patch also removes useless 'mock all' kind of test and replaces it with
a functional test.

Partially implements blueprint improve-dvr-l3-agent-binding

Change-Id: I6f56b0534e65bf036f4ebe34c51aef52c5859cd3

commit_message:
DVR: Add action specific functions for arp_entry_update

Update_arp_entry_for_dvr_service_port takes in an
argument for 'add' or 'del'.

This patch will provide two separate functions to
update and delete the arp entries instead of passing
in the action argument.

Co-Authored-By: John Schwarz <jschwarz@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I377591074d70ae81d4c46e990dc1ff106192ef69

commit_message:
Disable accounting procacct mode

Turn off process accounting ('no procacct' mode).
But atop still has an ability to collect valuable stats.

Bring in internal "custom_acct_file" option:
* false - use atop default accounting file
* /path_to/atop.acct - custom one
* undef - disable accounting procacct mode

DocImpact: 'custom_accounting_file' is system wide process
accounting file (valid values is above).

Change-Id: Ida00dc663dd8c6494c479de2ae2f0f7ab6014a84
Closes-Bug: #1530167

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-02-03 10:56:29.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/l2pop/rpc.py', 'neutron/tests/unit/plugins/ml2/drivers/l2pop/test_mech_driver.py'], 'message': "Get rid of marshall_fdb_entries

This function isn't necessary. The json encoding of a
named tuple will already turn into a normal list.

ports = [l2pop_rpc.PortInfo('abcdef', '1.1.1.1')]
json.dumps(ports) == json.dumps([(mac, ip) for (mac, ip) in ports])

An argument could be made that the PortInfo object could have
something added to it later that we wouldn't want to serialize
in order to remain backward compatible. However, doing so would
break all of the constructions of PortInfo objects on the agents
once they got the updated code for PortInfo that requires the
new parameter.

So there is no way currently to add a new field to PortInfo without
breaking existing legacy clients or breaking new clients.

serialization method used in oslo does not break on the named tuples.

Change-Id: I45ae69ef8c9c15ad21a28dc42f2d78b234ccfb0c
"}]
commit_message:
Get rid of marshall_fdb_entries

This function isn't necessary. The json encoding of a
named tuple will already turn into a normal list.

ports = [l2pop_rpc.PortInfo('abcdef', '1.1.1.1')]
json.dumps(ports) == json.dumps([(mac, ip) for (mac, ip) in ports])

An argument could be made that the PortInfo object could have
something added to it later that we wouldn't want to serialize
in order to remain backward compatible. However, doing so would
break all of the constructions of PortInfo objects on the agents
once they got the updated code for PortInfo that requires the
new parameter.

So there is no way currently to add a new field to PortInfo without
breaking existing legacy clients or breaking new clients.
Given that, let's stop doing the json encoder's job.

This patch also adds a sanity unit test to make sure the json
serialization method used in oslo does not break on the named tuples.

Change-Id: I45ae69ef8c9c15ad21a28dc42f2d78b234ccfb0c
